Commentary: short of length outside off, goes for the cut but cannot beat the man at cover
Commentary_short: Ndlovu to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, no run

Commentary: length ball, flatter around off, defended back
Commentary_short: Ndlovu to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, no run

Commentary: arm ball, coming in from a length around off, Gurbaz was looking to defend, gets an inside edge on to the pads
Commentary_short: Ndlovu to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, no run

Commentary: length outside off, cuts it towards point
Commentary_short: Ndlovu to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, no run

Commentary: goes for the slog sweep but gets a top edge that clears the short fine leg and lands safely
flatter on middle and leg, looks to pull but misses and is rapped on the pads
Commentary_short: Ndlovu to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, no run

Commentary: length ball around middle and leg, no room for Zazai who gets an inside edge onto his thigh
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Hazratullah Zazai, no run

Commentary: short and pulled away, Zazai rocks back and pulls it over deep midwicket, six right from the moment it hit the bat
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Hazratullah Zazai, SIX runs

Commentary: falls well short of the incoming third man. A touch fuller and wider outside off, Zazai went for the big heave but ended up slicing it towards third man
length ball around off, Gurbaz moves across and pulls it over deep square leg, for a 69 metre six
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, SIX runs

Commentary: short and wide, cuts hard but cannot beat the man in deep, a single to deep point
a slower one on the leg stump, Zazai was looking to work it on the leg side, the ball hits his thigh on lobs towards slip region
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Hazratullah Zazai, no run

Commentary: looped down on middle and off, tapped back to the bowler
Commentary_short: Williams to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, no run

Commentary: he backs away this time, hacking a big shot towards mid off
Commentary_short: Williams to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, no run

Commentary: quicker one, speared in towards his legs, Gurbaz walking across and paddling a sweep to short fine leg. A sloppy return from the fielder results in an overthrow
arm ball from Williams, on a length and headed in towards the pads
Commentary_short: Williams to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, no run

Commentary: boom! Gurbaz walks across again, changing the line of the delivery, and sends the ball over deep backward square with a pick-up slog sweep
Commentary_short: Williams to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, SIX runs

Commentary: worked off the pads, Williams sticking to a straight line, and a quick single to end the over
short ball to start, but an expansive pull is bottom edged down to fine leg

sloppy! Mpofu comes around the stumps and angles a length ball in to beat Zazai's heave to leg. Cracking delivery, but it catches Taylor on the wrong foot behind the stumps. He'd been moving to his left, and then dives right as the ball passes him
full and wide outside off now, and Zazai leans across to thump a square drive behind point with plenty of bottom hand
Commentary_short: Mpofu to Hazratullah Zazai, FOUR runs

Commentary: spliced, but safe! Another short one, and Zazai aims a slug down the ground. The ball takes the splice and lobs tamely towards mid on, dropping in front of him
Commentary_short: Mpofu to Hazratullah Zazai, no run

Commentary: another short one, another boundary. Mpofu angles a bouncer in and Zazai steps back, checking a scooped pull up and over short fine leg. He's got enough on it to easily beat the fielder
Commentary_short: Mpofu to Hazratullah Zazai, FOUR runs

Commentary: on a length, angling in, and he flicks to the midwicket fielder, in the ring
Commentary_short: Mpofu to Hazratullah Zazai, no run

Commentary: swatted over square leg, Gurbaz making the most of a long hop loosener by rocking back and hammering a pull over the boundary
Commentary_short: Ndlovu to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, SIX runs

Commentary: a much better length catches Gurbaz in the crease, the ball coming off the inside half of the blade and rolling to leg
speared in towards the pads from around the stumps, he misses a flick and it goes nowhere
Commentary_short: Ndlovu to Hazratullah Zazai, no run

Commentary: speared at the pads once more, and this time Zazai adds a little more vim to his swipe. Ball kisses bat, and runs away to fine leg. That was a freebie
Commentary_short: Ndlovu to Hazratullah Zazai, FOUR runs

Commentary: much better, floated up outside off and Zazai defends
Commentary_short: Ndlovu to Hazratullah Zazai, no run

Commentary: a big bottom-handed swing sends the ball bouncing out to Burl at deep midwicket, and up comes Afghanistan's fifty. The openers are in a hurry tonight

ouch! Zazai swats across the line at a length delivery, inside edges, and is struck amidships. He's down, and breathing hard. Eventually Zazai stands, but the ache has set in and he walks around gingerly. Eventually, he's good to go.
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Hazratullah Zazai, no run

Commentary: another length delivery shapes in towards Zazai's legs, and he toe-ends a big heave back to the bowler
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Hazratullah Zazai, no run

Commentary: slower ball, 110km/h, and pitched right up to him. Zazai taps to cover and they set off for a quick single
on a length and in the channel. Gurbaz angles towards point, and they chance another sprinted single
Jarvis rolls his fingers over another short one, Zazai aiming a pull out to Chakabva in the deep
a good over is spoiled. Gurbaz backs away and misses a hoick at a full one, but Jarvis has over-stepped. Or has he? Replays show that Jarvis actually had a sliver of heel behind the line
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, 1 no ball

Commentary: Gurbaz can't punish the Free Hit, smearing a length ball into the leg side, but nowhere near the middle of the bat
nicely bowled, Gurbaz is neither forward nor back as he pokes to cover
Commentary_short: Williams to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, no run

Commentary: accurate stuff, and there's no run to be had as Gurbaz flicks to midwicket
Commentary_short: Williams to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, no run

Commentary: quicker one, cramping him for room, and midwicket is in quickly to keep the batsmen at home
Commentary_short: Williams to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, no run

Commentary: a touch too full, and he drills a drive down to long off
much too short, and Zazai steps back and across to send a muscular pull over the deep midwicket boundary
Commentary_short: Williams to Hazratullah Zazai, SIX runs

Commentary: speared in flat and fast, outside off, Zazai cracks it back to the bowler
Commentary_short: Williams to Hazratullah Zazai, no run

Commentary: and he starts with a rank long hop, spinning away outside off. Long on and midwicket are on the ropes, but he picks the gap right between them with a lofted pull
Commentary_short: Burl to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, FOUR runs

Commentary: too short, and Gurbaz gets right underneath another lofted pull. He was aiming for the stands, and doesn't quite get the distance he's looking for, but enough on it to clear the rope
Commentary_short: Burl to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, SIX runs

Commentary: Gurbaz stays on the back foot, punching down to long off
slider, angling across him. Zazai has a look, and opts to defend
Commentary_short: Burl to Hazratullah Zazai, no run

Commentary: tapped down just wide of point, a single the result
nicely bowled, much more full and drawing him forward. But Gurbaz finds the gap at cover with an angled push, and keeps the strike
slower ball bouncer to start, dug in at 111km/h, and Gurbaz ducks under it
Commentary_short: Madziva to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, no run

Commentary: another slower one, this time a yorker that dips on him outside off. He drives off the toe of the bat to cover
Commentary_short: Madziva to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, no run

Commentary: dropped at deep midwicket! It's Chakabva out there. Gurbaz slogged a length delivery high, but almost straight out to him. Chakabva settles under it, but the ball pops straight through his cupped hands and dribbles over the rope
Commentary_short: Madziva to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, FOUR runs

Commentary: another slower ball, on a length and out of the back of the hand. Gurbaz mis-reads it and swings over the top of it as the ball bursts past his off stump
Commentary_short: Madziva to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, no run

Commentary: full pace delivery, very full outside off, and it's dug out to cover
very slow cutter, down to 101km/h, and Zazai pulls off the front foot out to deep midwicket
full, on his legs, and it's slugged out to wide long on
pushed through flat on off stump at 92km/h, on the drive down to long off

top edge, and this one is held! Zazai bent down low to set himself for a slog sweep, but the ball bounced a little more than he was expecting, ballooning off the top edge. Mutumbami settles under it at short third man, and holds a simple chance
Dismissal_text: Hazratullah Zazai c Mutumbami b Mutombodzi 31 (24b 3x4 2x6) SR: 129.16

Commentary: quicker ball, out of the front of the hands, and it's tapped to point
Commentary_short: Mutombodzi to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, no run

Commentary: floated up full outside off, and a drive brings a single to long off

beaten! Beautiful googly from Mutombodzi. Shafiqullah didn't have a clue as he groped forward, the ball spinning in through a big gap between bat and pad. Fortunately for him, it scoots just past the stumps
very full, dug out to cover
Commentary_short: Ndlovu to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, no run

Commentary: uses his feet this time, getting close to the ball and driving to long on
held back a touch, and spinning away outside off. Tapped back to the bowler
this one goes on with the arm, squirting off the inside half of the bat into the leg side. The fielders are deep, and they push very hard for a second

dropped! This was a very tough chance though. Shafiqullah slogs in the air, and Chakabva has plenty of ground to make, running in and around from deep midwicket. He dives forward, and gets the fingers to it, but can't hold on. Good effort
confusion! It's tapped to cover, one batsman wants a single and the other doesn't. Gurbaz is late being sent back, but the throw isn't quite on target. A better throw would have had him
Commentary_short: Ndlovu to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, no run

Commentary: up and over cover, driven in the air. Shafiqullah spotted a full one, outside off, and aimed his drive for the gap between long off and cover
he's almost done in the flight by a full one, but manages to put bat to ball on a paddle sweep
quicker one, short outside off, but he can't capitalize as the cut is stopped at point
slog swept into the leg side, the ball skidding along the turf into the deep, where Burl dives at midwicket to save runs
handsomely driven, Shafiqullah's eyes lighting up as Tino offers up another full, wide one. Deliberately lifted over wide long off, and up comes the hundred
angled to point, who is in quickly to stop the single
slow cutter, on the stumps, Gurbaz whips across his front pad to raise a maiden T20I fifty
short ball, rising over leg stump, and he swivels into a pull down to fine leg
Gurbaz backs away, Mpofu follows him with a back of a length delivery. But he lays bat on a swat to leg, picking the gap too
Commentary_short: Mpofu to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, FOUR runs

Commentary: another short one, but the pull is bottom edged into the leg side. Possibly tried to hit it a bit too hard
bumper, once again, and it fizzes past a wild pull, thudding into Taylor's gloves

big appeal, and it's given! Shafiqullah was aiming for a slog sweep, but swung past the ball, which hit him on the upper thigh. He was down on one knee in front of the stumps, and adjacent by the looks of things. But he asks for a review, which only serves to confirm the dismissal. No bat on it, three reds, and that's plumb
slogged out towards long on, and the fielder is a little slow getting in off the rope, the ball dropping well in front of him
glanced off the pads, just wide of short fine leg
reverse sweep, over point and it bounces away. Gurbaz turned himself around and lifted it cleanly over the infield
Commentary_short: Williams to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, FOUR runs

Commentary: caught at cover, but it's a no ball! That is a massive error. Gurbaz sliced his drive into Masakadza's hands, but Williams has over stepped and rather than a wicket, it's a Free Hit
Commentary_short: Williams to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, 1 no ball

Commentary: fired in full and fast, and he can't quite put it away, just the single to cover
short and wide outside off, and it's cut out to the cover sweeper

now he gets him! Gurbaz walks across to the off side but leaves his stumps exposed, Williams firing in a full ball that scoots behind his legs and clatters into the timber. The umpire asks them to have another look for the no-ball ... but this one is a legitimate delivery, just! Williams really pushing the line though
almost chopped on! Mpofu angles one in from around the stumps, and Najibullah bottom edges his cut just past the stumps
Commentary_short: Mpofu to Najibullah Zadran, no run

Commentary: and now he beats the drive outside off. It was a slower ball, well wide of off, and Najibullah drove over the top of it
Commentary_short: Mpofu to Najibullah Zadran, no run

Commentary: short, and he splices an aerial pull out towards long on. 'Catch it!' Mpofu shouts, but it's well short of the fielder

top edged, over the keeper! Nabi didn't know too much about this. It was a slower bouncer, and he played too early at it, taking his eyes off the ball, which strikes the bat - or is his helmet? - and flies over Taylor's head for four
Commentary_short: Mpofu to Mohammad Nabi, FOUR runs

Commentary: caught at short fine leg, simple chance. Three wickets in three overs, and Zimbabwe are clawing their way back. Mpofu delivers another slower cutter, on his legs, and Nabi top edges his flick into the leg side. Jarvis takes a few steps in from fine leg, and makes no mistake
Dismissal_text: Mohammad Nabi c Jarvis b Mpofu 4 (2b 1x4 0x6) SR: 200.00

Commentary: angled in to him, and rising off a length. Najibullah hops and fends towards midwicket for a quick single
tapped down just wide of point, quick single
floaty, low full toss on his legs, and it's clipped down to long on to get off the mark

a big heave, sliced and caught! Tino delivers a googly, going across him and taking the top edge of Najibullah's slog sweep. Madziva and Mutumbami are both interested in the catch, but it's Madziva, running across from short third man, who calls for it and holds on
Dismissal_text: Najibullah Zadran c Madziva b Mutombodzi 5 (8b 0x4 0x6) SR: 62.50

Commentary: another low full toss, and it's tapped to cover
Commentary_short: Mutombodzi to Fazal Niazai, no run

Commentary: googly, spinning in to him, and Niazai picks it at the last moment, defending to point
Commentary_short: Mutombodzi to Fazal Niazai, no run

Commentary: slogged into the leg side, but it's poorly timed and just the single. But his international account is now open
nicely bowled, angling in to him, and it's pushed softly to cover
Commentary_short: Ndlovu to Fazal Niazai, no run

Commentary: off the inside half of the bat now, the ball rushing straight on, and it bounces down to fine leg
very full, nicely straight, and he drives to long on
crunched down to long on, one more
speared in full, and he drives to cover
Commentary_short: Williams to Fazal Niazai, no run

Commentary: dug in back to Williams, who fires a throw back to the keeper
Commentary_short: Williams to Fazal Niazai, no run

Commentary: clears long on! Pitched up, and Gulbadin holds nothing back on the drive. He gets enough on it to beat Burl down at the boundary's edge
Commentary_short: Williams to Gulbadin Naib, SIX runs

Commentary: tapped to leg, and Williams himself sets after it, keeping them to one
pulled away, in the air but falling well short of Mutumbami in the deep
very full, aimed at the stumps, and he drives down to long on
slower ball bouncer, and it loops up and past Gulbadin's pull
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Gulbadin Naib, no run

Commentary: this time it's the full pace bouncer, and it rushes on to him, hurrying another attempted pull. The ball bursts off the splice, and Ndlovu holds the skied catch at deep midwicket
Dismissal_text: Gulbadin Naib c Ndlovu b Jarvis 10 (7b 0x4 1x6) SR: 142.85

Commentary: no ball, and it's slashed away! Jarvis over steps as he delivers a full, wide one outside off that is slashed down to third man. Free Hit coming up ...
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Fazal Niazai, (no ball) FOUR runs

Commentary: slow legcutter, 113km/h, and it's cracked to Burl at point

slow bouncer, jammed into the pitch. Rashid buckles his knees as it rises past his pull. There's some confusion as the square leg umpire calls no-ball, thinking Jarvis had bowled too many bouncers in the over. But it's the first one, as the bowler himself points out
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Rashid Khan, no run

Commentary: offcutter, on the stumps, and it's punched down to long on

down the track comes Rashid, swatting a short one over wide long on with a fierce tennis-style forehand. It pings out of the middle, and over a leaping fielder near the boundary. And that brings up the 150
Commentary_short: Mpofu to Rashid Khan, SIX runs

Commentary: an inside edged heave brings a single to fine leg
Mpofu has another! He delivers a slower cutter, full and outside off. Niazai aims for the stands down the ground, but can't get enough on it, Burl holding a regulation chance down at long on
Dismissal_text: Fazal Niazai c Burl b Mpofu 12 (15b 1x4 0x6) SR: 80.00

Commentary: Mpofu pushes his line wide outside off, Rashid fetching the ball down to long on for a single

gone first ball! Asghar has come in down the order, and fallen first ball. The ball was full and wide outside off, and he sliced underneath it to present a steepling chance to Ndlovu, running back from short third man. He tumbles over as he takes the catch, but holds on to give Mpofu his career-best figures in this format
Dismissal_text: Asghar Afghan c Ndlovu b Mpofu 0 (1b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0.00

Commentary: cracking finish from Mpofu, delivering another full, wide delivery that beats Rashid's booming drive
Commentary_short: Mpofu to Rashid Khan, no run

Commentary: starts with a fuller one straying down the leg side, Taylor sweeps it fine and beats the man at 45
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Taylor, FOUR runs

Commentary: goes down the ground this time, it was fuller on the stumps, Taylor took a big stride forward and lofted it over long-on for a six
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Taylor, SIX runs

Commentary: length ball on the stumps, dabs it towards short midwicket and sets off for one
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Taylor, 1 run

Commentary: a googly around off, too full, pushed back towards the bowler
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Masakadza, no run

Commentary: another googly, length around off and Masakadza helps it behind square leg, off the mark
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Masakadza, 1 run

Commentary: length ball on the leg stump, Taylor was looking to nudge it on the leg side, misses and it lobs behind square off the thigh
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Taylor, no run

Commentary: length ball on the stumps, looks to push towards midwicket, an inside edge on to the pads and they sneak in a single as the ball rolls towards the leg side
length ball around off, a bit seam movement away, defended from the crease
Commentary_short: Dawlat Zadran to Taylor, no run

Commentary: length ball around off, goes for the cut but ends up bottom-edging it past the stumps, a single to fine leg
length ball on the stumps, whipped past midwicket, Rashid Khan puts in the chase and keeps it to two
fuller on the stumps, goes down on one knee and sweeps it over fine leg, all the way for a six
Commentary_short: Dawlat Zadran to Masakadza, SIX runs

Commentary: fuller on the stumps and swinging in, Masakadza gets his pad away and flicks it towards deep square leg
length ball around off, Masakadza skips down but cannot reach to the pitch, pushed towards the bowler
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Masakadza, no run

Commentary: length ball around off, steered towards cover-point for one
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Masakadza, 1 run

Commentary: length ball on the stumps, lunges forward and defends
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Taylor, no run

Commentary: length ball around off, stays in his crease and taps it back
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Taylor, no run

Commentary: length ball around off, swings across but the bottom hand comes off the handle, a single to deep square leg
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Taylor, 1 run

Commentary: flatter and quicker on the pads, tucked away behind square leg
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Masakadza, 1 run

Commentary: length ball around off, forced off the back foot but the mid-off makes a tumbling stop to his left

a bit of confusion, direct hit would have been curtains for Masakadza. Was a length ball around off, Taylor moved across and looked to glance it fine. The ball lobs towards short fine leg off the thigh via an inside edge. Masakadza was already halfway down but the fielder misses his shy at the bowler's end
Commentary_short: Dawlat Zadran to Taylor, no run

Commentary: short of length outside off, stays back and slaps it through covers for four
Commentary_short: Dawlat Zadran to Taylor, FOUR runs

Commentary: fuller outside off, clears his front leg and looks to smash it over the bowler's head, misses
Commentary_short: Dawlat Zadran to Taylor, no run

Commentary: length ball on the stumps, tucked away towards square leg
short of length on the stumps, Masakadza rocks back and pulls it over deep-backward square leg for his second six of the night
Commentary_short: Dawlat Zadran to Masakadza, SIX runs

Commentary: length ball on middle and leg and going down, Taylor looks to pull but it keeps low and hits the batsman on the pads
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Taylor, no run

Commentary: length ball on the stumps, chipped towards the right of Nabi at mid-on
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Taylor, 1 run

Commentary: another googly, flatter and hurries on the batsman, Masakadza was looking to pull it away but gets cramped
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Masakadza, no run

Commentary: length ball on the stumps, pushed towards mid-on for a quick single
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Masakadza, 1 run

Commentary: length ball on the stumps, Taylor backs away to push it on the off side but gets beaten and it bounces just over the stumps. Replays show there was an edge as well but the keeper failed to latch on to it
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Taylor, no run

Commentary: he gets his man this time, was a length ball on the stumps, Taylor goes for the heave but fails to clear Najibullah at deep midwicket
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Taylor, OUT
Dismissal_text: BRM Taylor c Najibullah Zadran b Mujeeb Ur Rahman 19 (17b 2x4 1x6) SR: 111.76

Commentary: short of length outside off, pushes it towards deep cover, a bit of fumble there but doesn't cost
length ball on the stumps, flicked towards midwicket from the front foot
Commentary_short: Gulbadin Naib to Chakabva, no run

Commentary: length ball outside off, around fifth stump, left alone
Commentary_short: Gulbadin Naib to Chakabva, no run

Commentary: length ball around off, comes forward and defends it on the off side
Commentary_short: Gulbadin Naib to Chakabva, no run

Commentary: fuller around off, tucked away in front of square leg to get off the mark
length ball around off, punched between the bowler and the non-striker for one
length but down the leg side, starts with a wide
length ball on the pads, flicked away towards deep square leg
slower in the air once again but fuller down the leg side, worked towards square leg for one
into the stands! A length ball around off, Masakadza skips down and lofts it way over wide long-on, brings up the fifty for Zimbabwe
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nabi to Masakadza, SIX runs

Commentary: short of length on the stumps, goes back and punches it towards short midwicket
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nabi to Masakadza, no run

Commentary: short again, goes back and pulls it towards the right of long-on
length ball pitching on the leg stump and spinning down, another wide
slower again but much better line this time, tossed up outside off, spins in big to beat the bat and hit the batsman on thigh
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nabi to Chakabva, no run

Commentary: almost ends up hitting it to short fine leg, was a length ball on the stumps, Masakadza tried to repeat his slog lap but didn't middle it at all, falls short and to the left of short fine leg
fuller around off, pushed towards extra cover for a quick single
a slower one this time, short of length on the stumps, pulls it towards deep square leg
length ball around off, shuffles a bit in the crease and just taps it towards midwicket, scampers back for the second
another slower one around off, tapped between square leg and midwicket but the fielder from deep square leg was quick to the ball this time and keeps it to one
fuller outside off, goes down on one knee and sweeps to to the left of short fine leg, along the ground this time
Commentary_short: Gulbadin Naib to Masakadza, FOUR runs

Commentary: length ball around off, pushed towards short midwicket for a quick single
short of length around off, rocks back and pulls it straight down the ground, long-on had no chance to cut it off
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nabi to Masakadza, FOUR runs

Commentary: down the track but Nabi has bowled it a touch slower, Masakadza didn't reach to the pitch, neither he middled it but it still clears the long-off, his fourth six of the innings
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nabi to Masakadza, SIX runs

Commentary: flatter outside off, goes back and cuts it towards deep backward point, comes back for the second
length ball on the stumps, stays back and taps it towards square leg
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nabi to Masakadza, no run

Commentary: short of length outside off, punches it towards extra cover, the fielder makes a diving effort and gets a hand to it but Masakadza not only completes his fifty but also hares back for the second
fuller on the stumps, pushed towards midwicket for one
a googly, short of length around off, goes back and punches it towards the bowler
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to Masakadza, no run

Commentary: fuller around off, comes forward and drives it towards long-on
length ball on the pads, glanced towards fine leg for one
short of length on the stumps, goes for the pull but gets an inside edge through his legs towards fine leg
length ball on the stumps, works it towards short fine leg
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to Chakabva, no run

Commentary: length ball on the stumps, punched towards long-on
length ball on the pads, flicked towards deep-backward square leg
fuller and down the leg side, Masakadza was looking to go for another lap sleep but cannot reach there

a slower length ball around off, Masakadza picks it up and forces it over the bowler's head from the back foot, mid-off was onside the circle and can just watch it go towards the boundary line. These two have added 50 now off 36, Chakabva contribution is only ten
Commentary_short: Fazal Niazai to Masakadza, FOUR runs

Commentary: fuller on the leg stumps, almost in the blockhole, gets his bat down and manages to dig it out towards deep square leg
length ball on the stumps, Chakabva gets into the action this time, moves across and scoops it over short fine leg
Commentary_short: Fazal Niazai to Chakabva, FOUR runs

Commentary: another slower length ball, a little bit wider this time, Chakabva moves across and places it towards midwicket
fuller around off, a little shimmy down the ground to reach to the pitch and work it towards midwicket
length ball on the stumps, punched back towards Rashid
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to Masakadza, no run

Commentary: a googly on the stumps, a touch fuller, clears his front leg and drills his down the ground, long-on puts in the slide but fails to stop that
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to Masakadza, FOUR runs

Commentary: dropped short this time and Masakadza is not going to miss out. Rocks back and pulls it over deep midwicket
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to Masakadza, SIX runs

Commentary: fuller around off, digs it out towards extra cover
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to Masakadza, no run

Commentary: fuller on the stumps, pushes it towards long-on for one
length ball around off, looks to smash it over the bowler's head but misses
